  "prompt": "What are the other healthcare compliance enforced other than HIPAA in Unites states of America?",
  "response": "In the United States, there are several healthcare compliance regulations besides HIPAA:\n\n1. Federal Regulations:\n- False Claims Act (FCA)\n- Patient Safety and Quality Improvement Act (PSQIA)\n- Emergency Medical Treatment and Active Labor Act (EMTALA)\n- Medicare/Medicaid Fraud Prevention Laws\n- Anti-Kickback Statute\n- Stark Law\n- 42 CFR Part 2 (Substance Abuse Confidentiality)\n\n2. Data Privacy Regulations:\n- HITECH Act\n- GDPR (for international data handling)\n- California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)\n\n3. Security Compliance:\n- NIST Cybersecurity Framework\n- HITRUST CSF\n- SOC 2 Compliance\n- FDA Medical Device Security Regulations\n\n4. State-Level Regulations:\n- California Privacy Rights Act (CPRA)\n- New York SHIELD Act\n- Texas Medical Records Privacy Act\n- Massachusetts Data Protection Law\n\n5. Clinical Research Compliance:\n- Common Rule\n- FDA Regulations\n- Good Clinical Practice (GCP) Guidelines\n\n6. Patient Rights Regulations:\n- Patient Self-Determination Act\n- Affordable Care Act (ACA) provisions\n\nThese regulations aim to protect patient data, ensure quality care, prevent fraud, and maintain healthcare standards.",
